CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1956, pg. 3 reads: "Cute 'Honeybunnies' Paraded... and captured the hears of everyone at the fashion show at A. Leo Weil School. Wearing perky spring outfits with sparkling smiles on their faces, some came out in pairs, as a single, or in one instance, as a trio.  Left to right:...Maria and Victoria Taylor..."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Maria and Victoria Taylor modeling identical light colored dresses, standing on stage in A. Leo Weil School for Easter fashion show
